Edition:
Quote: Since our arrival a great number of the new [sic] Zealanders have come from different parts of the Sound and taken up their abode in Ship Cove - we were now busily employ'd in cutting Wood compleating our Water - brewing Spruce Beer - boiling down the Blubber we got at the Island of Desolation, making Hay, repairing our rigging Sails &c.
Notes: 1777 Feb 12 Thomas Edgar's Log in 1908 McNab Historical Records 2/227

